title: The King's Singers Atlantic Bridge 1979
description:
The King's Singers Atlantic Bridge is an album containing folk songs and spirituals from both sides of the Atlantic.  It was recorded and released in 1979.

Track Listing:
	1. Ring De Banjo
	2. Swing Low Swee Chariot
	3. Dry Bones
	4. Shenandoah
	5. Nobody Knows
	6. Keep In The Middle of the Road
	7. Beautiful Dreamer
	8. Coming Through The Rye
	9. Oh Susanna
	10. Annie Laurie
	11. Joshua Fit De Battle Of Jericho
	12. Jeanie With The Light Brown Hair
	13. Standing in the Need of Prayer
	14. Danny Boy
	15. The Last Rose of Summer
	16. Home on the Range

The King's Singers:
	Nigel Perrin & Alastair Hume - Counter Tenors
	Bill (Greyston) Ives - Tenor
	Anthony Holt & Simon Carrington - Baritones
	Brian Kay - Bass

This album is no longer available for purchase either as a CD or download, though it may be found on eBay or Amazon.  Annie Laurie and Danny Boy may be found on other albums.

This album recording was slightly over modulated so there will be some distortion.  I tried to keep it at a minimum, but then I couldn't hear the soft spots.  

As this is from vinyl hiss and pop will be evident.  No processing was performed on the tracks except to edit out silence before and after the tracks.

This was recoded using Cool Edit Pro then saved as a 128k mp3.
